habitat_description:
Ashton and Ashton (1985) reported the introduction and establishment of both parthenogenetic and bisexually reproducing morphotypes in Miami, Florida. Originally, the range of this species in Central America extends from Guatemala through Colombia, Venezuela, and Honduras (Conant and Collins 1998; Maslin and Secoy 1986). Its introduction to Florida presumably occurred through interacting subspecies on Islas de la Bahia, Honduras; Aves Island, Blanquilla Island, and Margarita Island, Venezuela (Sites et al. 1990; Vyas et al. 1990).

This species is found in grassland, savanna, suburban and orchard habitats. It also inhabits heavily disturbed areas like beaches, urban settings, industrial areas, railroad edges, roadways, and crop fields (Ashton and Ashton 1985; Serena 1984).
